# {{APP_NAME}}

Scaffolded by [`bare-kit-pear`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/bare-kit-pear).
Native iOS shell (SwiftUI) on top of a Bare backend worklet.

## Build

```bash
npm install --save-dev react-native-bare-kit bare-pack
npm run ios:setup   # fetch BareKit + mirror addons + bundle backend
npm run ios:build   # xcodegen + xcodebuild for simulator
```

Install + launch on the booted simulator:

```bash
xcrun simctl install booted \
  "$HOME/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData/{{APP_NAME}}-"*"/Build/Products/Debug-iphonesimulator/{{APP_NAME}}.app"
xcrun simctl launch booted com.{{APP_NAME}}
```

## Add a native SwiftUI screen

Drop a new file under `ios-native/{{APP_NAME}}/Sources/App/`. Xcodegen
globs the directory — rerun `xcodegen generate`. Reach the backend via
`@EnvironmentObject var host: AppHost` + `host.rpc?.request(...)`.

## Add a new backend command

1. Add a case to `Cmd` in `Sources/RPC/Protocol.swift`.
2. Add the matching integer to the backend's rpc dispatcher
   (typically `backend/index.js`).
3. Return `{ id, result }` or `{ id, error }` — framing is automatic.

Event IDs go in `Evt` + a matching emitter on the backend.

